      "content": "This issue highlights a common concern in the academic publishing landscape known as the 'Northern ascendancy' problem. To address this, you may want to explore tweaks to the acceptance rate weights, potentially incorporating author hubs or institutions from the Global South to receive more visibility. Another option could be to introduce diversity metrics, such as historical citation data or impact factor adjustments, to down-weight influential journals that have biased acceptance rates. This would help promote more diverse voices and actively challenge the existing power dynamics in the field.",
